<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9029&amp;p=105448#p105448"><![CDATA[
I also once had this idea. Rice's plugin does something similiar for n64, it dumps textures to a folder -those can be edited and then get loaded when you run the game.<br /><br />Raine emu also does something similar with a few arcade games. <br /><br />If something like this could be applied to nes, maybe an emu with a tile dumper, then when the game loads it uses those tiles. <br /><br />Maybe take it another step and 2x the tiles, and adjust the screen w/h. Having tiles 2x in size would really make it easier to make amazing looking edited sprites.<br /><br />Possible? what do you guys think?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5821">net44</a> — Thu Jan 03, 2013 2:08 am</p><hr />
